# Domain Layer Purity

The Domain project is pure C# — no infrastructure or framework dependencies.

## Allowed

- Entities, value objects, domain enums, domain exceptions
- `System.*` and BCL types only
- `BaseCrud.Abstractions` and `BaseCrud` packages (`EntityBase<Guid>`, `ISelectExpression`, DTO markers)
- Business invariants enforced inside entities (factory methods)

## Forbidden

- EF Core attributes or `DbContext` references
- ASP.NET Core types
- NuGet packages except `BaseCrud.Abstractions` and `BaseCrud` (see Allowed)
- References to Application, Infrastructure, or API projects
- Interface implementations for external services

## Entity Pattern

```csharp
// GOOD
public class FileItem
{
    public Guid Id { get; private set; }
    public string Name { get; private set; } = null!;

    private FileItem() { }

    public static FileItem CreateFile(string name, Guid ownerId, Guid? parentId)
    {
        // validate invariants here
        return new FileItem { /* ... */ };
    }
}

// BAD — public setters, direct construction from outside
public class FileItem
{
    public Guid Id { get; set; }
}
// var file = new FileItem(); // never expose public ctor for creation
```

## Naming

Use English for all types, members, and comments.
